      "comment": "FRANCO NICKELBACK NZ (10) is a progressive gelding who cruised home on debut before working but toughing out a win at this circuit and distance last start. Draws on the back line for the first time but could be bound for better things. WAMBOYNE MACHETE (9) last appeared when a fourth at Albury in December, capping off a fine prep that saw him salute on four occasions. Should enjoy a pretty soft run from this draw with the sprint lane in play. Has trialled so expecting a bright start to the campaign. MY ULTIMATE FRANCO NZ (7) draws wider but was very impressive when cruising to a last-start win by 30 metres at this venue. MILLIE FRANCIS NZ (3) worked when fourth as a hot favourite last time but did well to overcome a back row draw for a Canberra win prior.",
